===Etymology 2===
From {{etyl|fr|en}} {{m|fr|bombarder}}, from {{etyl|frm|en}} {{m|frm|bombarde||a bombard}}

====Verb====
{{en-verb}}

# To continuously [[attack]] something with [[bomb]]s, [[artillery]] [[shell]]s or other [[missile]]s or [[projectile]]s.
#: {{ux|en|The enemy's stronghold was '''bombarded''' for 3 hours straight.}}
# {{lb|en|figuratively}} To attack something or someone by [[directing]] objects at them.
# {{lb|en|figuratively}} To continuously send or direct (at someone)
#: {{ux|en|I was '''bombarded''' with WhatsApp messages after appearing on the news.}}
#: {{ux|en|Please don't '''bombard''' me with questions right now, I'll answer them at the end of the statement.}}
# {{lb|en|physics}} To direct at a [[substance]] an [[intense]] [[stream]] of high-energy [[particle]]s, usually sub-atomic or made of at most a few atoms.

